Item Description:
Heal the Bay will continue to serve as the Adopt-A-Beach coordinator for
Los Angeles County.  As part of the Adopt-A-Beach program, Heal the
Bay will enable participation of underserved elementary, middle, and
high school students by providing bus transportation to the beach for 15
trips, as well as a free educational presentation at each school about
ocean pollution and beach safety from a member of Heal the Bays
trained Speakers Bureau.  Heal the Bay will also maintain an
interactive marine debris database. This past year 37,497 volunteers
participated in 654 cleanups at 50 different sites within Los Angeles
County.  Heal the Bay expects to serve similar numbers during this
grant period.
